articles.title: Five Fun Facts!
articles.description: Five Fun Facts about Alyssa Columbus
articles.contents:
I enjoy spending time outdoors, especially by the ocean.
I also enjoy birdwatching. My favorite birds are Cedar
Waxwings.
One of my hobbies is competing in online cybersecurity (i.e.,
Capture the Flag) competitions.
I enjoy volunteering, especially for the Girl Scouts.
I am the founder of the
Irvine, CA chapter of R-Ladies Global.

            Introduction
            My name is Alyssa Columbus, and I am a first-year
            Biostatistics PhD student at the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg
            School of Public Health. Before starting my PhD, I
            worked professionally as a data scientist, information
            security analyst, and consultant. I have also conducted
            research on topics including breast cancer risk assessment
            models and neural implementations of survival analyses for
            circadian rhythms. I hold a bachelor’s degree in Mathematics
            from the University of California,
            Irvine and a master’s degree in Applied and
            Computational Mathematics from Johns Hopkins
            University.
            In this course, I look forward to learning more about how
            statistical computing tools and workflows are used in
            academic contexts.
            
            Additional Information
            Five fun facts about me can be found on the “Fun Facts” page.
            “A Cool Link”
            redirects to the R Graph Gallery, which provides code
            snippets and previews of many visualizations that can be
            made with R. I’ve included this resource here because I’ve
            used it many times, and it may be helpful for other students
            in this course.
